div.h1: OS Debugging: QEMU + GDB + Serial Pipeline

li.p: Check last serial output -> shows EIP before crash
In GDB, set catch point: catch signal SIGTRAP continue
Examine CPU state at crash: info registers x/20x $esp
Check IDT validity: x/256x &idt_entries info idt (QEMU monitor)

div.p: (qemu) info registers # full CPU state (qemu) info tss # TSS content (qemu) info idt # IDT entries (qemu) info mem # page tables (qemu) xp /20x 0x100000 # physical memory (qemu) savevm crash # snapshot state
target remote localhost:1234 symbol file: kernel.elf
x/10i $pc # 10 instructions x/20x $esp # stack dump info registers # all regs info tss # TSS content
si # single instruction ni # step over call finish # run until return
[0x00100000] kernel_entry: EIP=0x100000 [0x00100034] idt_load: IDTR=0x10800 [0x00100200] context_switch: PID 1 -> 2 [TRIPLE FAULT] last EIP=0x00102340

#define DUMP_REGS()
serial_printf("EAX=%x EBX=%x ECX=%x\n",
eax, ebx, ecx)

g.text: Page fault in page fault handler

div.p: gdb kernel.elf (gdb) target remote :1234 (gdb) break kernel_main (gdb) continue
(gdb) si # step (gdb) x/10i $pc # disassemble (gdb) info registers # check state (gdb) continue # run more
